# iOS UI/UX Agent Scope

## Allowed

- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Views/` ‚Äî SwiftUI screens and components
- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/ViewModels/` ‚Äî e.g. `OutfitViewModel.swift`
- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Services/` ‚Äî `APIService.swift`, `AuthService.swift` (contract changes only)
- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Models/` ‚Äî Codable DTOs (contract changes only)
- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Utils/` ‚Äî shared helpers
- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Theme/AppTheme.swift` ‚Äî design tokens

## Forbidden

- `frontend/**` ‚Äî web agent owns this
- `backend/**` ‚Äî orchestrator or backend step owns this
- `ios-client/build-device/**`, `**/xcuserdata/**` ‚Äî build artifacts

## Architecture

Views ‚Üí ViewModels ‚Üí Services ‚Üí Models. Keep views declarative; state and API calls in ViewModels.

## Styling

- Use `AppTheme` for colors, gradients, glass surfaces (mirrors web palette)
- SwiftUI: `TabView`, `NavigationStack`, sheets for modals
- Reference: `ios-client/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`, `IOS_CLIENT_SUMMARY.md`

## Platform-specific (keep on iOS)

- Keychain via `TokenStorage.swift` for JWT
- `AppConfig.swift` for API base URL
- Native image picker, haptics, accessibility identifiers

## Parity

Behavior and copy must match the active spec and web implementation. Sync contract files with web when models, API calls, or progress steps change.

## iPhone / iPad parity (required)

Keep iPhone and iPad UX **the same** ‚Äî one app, not two designs.

### Same on all devices

- Navigation (`TabView` + `NavigationStack`) ‚Äî no iPad-only sidebar or `NavigationSplitView`
- Flows, copy, buttons, auth gates, and API behavior
- Feature availability (no iPad-only or iPhone-only features)

### Layout-only differences (allowed)

Use `@Environment(\.horizontalSizeClass)` or `.adaptiveContent(maxWidth:)` ‚Äî **never** `UIDevice` / `userInterfaceIdiom` checks for UX branching.

| Allowed | Avoid |
|---------|--------|
| Max content width (e.g. 980‚Äì1080pt on regular width) | Different screens or navigation per device |
| Slightly larger images / spacing | Different labels, actions, or flows |
| Horizontal toolbar when regular width (e.g. History search row) | Split-view master/detail |
| Adaptive grid column minimums (same cards) | iPad-only feature flags |

**Rule:** Adapt **layout**, not **behavior**. If a change would feel different on iPad vs iPhone beyond spacing/width, it needs explicit product approval in the spec.

### Existing patterns (reuse)

- `AppTheme.adaptiveContent(maxWidth:)` ‚Äî cap width on regular horizontal size class
- `isRegularWidth` (`horizontalSizeClass == .regular`) ‚Äî minor layout tweaks in `MainFlowView`, `WardrobeListView`, `HistoryListView`, `OutfitSuggestionView`

## About & Guide (Twin UI ‚Äî when spec requires)

- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Views/UserGuideView.swift` ‚Äî step-by-step walkthroughs
- `ios-client/OutfitSuggestor/Views/AboutView.swift` ‚Äî feature list and app description
- Update when user-visible flows, copy, or capabilities change; keep aligned with web Guide/About
- Skip for layout-only tweaks

## Tests (Twin UI ‚Äî required)

- Unit/Integration: `ios-client/OutfitSuggestorTests/`
- UITest (critical E2E only): `ios-client/OutfitSuggestorUITests/`
- Run build + new test classes before returning
- Assert new behavior from spec ‚Äî build-only is not sufficient when logic changed
